data.name: Bitterblossom
data.oracle_text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you lose 1 life and create a 1/1 black Faerie Rogue creature token with flying.
data.flavor_text: In Lorwyn's brief evenings, the sun pauses at the horizon long enough for a certain species of violet to bloom with the fragrance of mischief.

data.name: All Is Dust
data.oracle_text: Each player sacrifices all permanents they control that are one or more colors.
data.flavor_text:
"The emergence of the Eldrazi isn't necessarily a bad thing, as long as you've already lived a fulfilling and complete life without regrets."
—Javad Nasrin, Ondu relic hunter

data.name: Eldrazi Conscription
data.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +10/+10 and has trample and annihilator 2. (Whenever it attacks, defending player sacrifices two permanents.)
data.flavor_text: The barest taste of Eldrazi power shatters both realms and identities.

data.name: Eyes of the Wisent
data.oracle_text: Whenever an opponent casts a blue spell during your turn, you may create a 4/4 green Elemental creature token.
data.flavor_text:
Calm as a wisent's watch
—Elvish expression meaning "safe"

data.name: Favor of the Mighty
data.oracle_text: Each creature with the highest mana value has protection from all colors.
data.flavor_text:
"What does a mountain fear of a fly? Giants are barely aware of us, let alone afraid."
—Gaddock Teeg

data.name: Hoofprints of the Stag
data.oracle_text:
Whenever you draw a card, you may put a hoofprint counter on Hoofprints of the Stag.
{2}{W}, Remove four hoofprint counters from Hoofprints of the Stag: Create a 4/4 white Elemental creature token with flying. Activate only during your turn.

data.name: Knowledge Exploitation
data.oracle_text:
Prowl {3}{U} (You may cast this for its prowl cost if you dealt combat damage to a player this turn with a Rogue.)
Search target opponent's library for an instant or sorcery card. You may cast that card without paying its mana cost. Then that player shuffles.

data.name: Militia's Pride
data.oracle_text: Whenever a nontoken creature you control attacks, you may pay {W}. If you do, create a 1/1 white Kithkin Soldier creature token that's tapped and attacking.
data.flavor_text: If you pick a fight with one kithkin, be ready to fight them all.

data.name: Notorious Throng
data.oracle_text:
Prowl {5}{U} (You may cast this for its prowl cost if you dealt combat damage to a player this turn with a Rogue.)
Create X 1/1 black Faerie Rogue creature tokens with flying, where X is the damage dealt to your opponents this turn. If this spell's prowl cost was paid, take an extra turn after this one.

data.name: Altar of the Goyf
data.oracle_text:
Whenever a creature you control attacks alone, it gets +X/+X until end of turn, where X is the number of card types among cards in all graveyards.
Lhurgoyf creatures you control have trample.
data.flavor_text:
"What dies grows the [illegible]"
—Clawed-out statue instription

data.name: Boggart Shenanigans
data.oracle_text: Whenever another Goblin you control is put into a graveyard from the battlefield, you may have Boggart Shenanigans deal 1 damage to target player or planeswalker.
data.set_name: Duel Decks Anthology: Elves vs. Goblins
data.flavor_text: Boggarts revel in discovering new sensations, from the texture of an otter pellet to the squeak of a dying warren mate.

data.name: Cloak and Dagger
Diviner's Wand
Ego Erasure
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Creatures target player controls get -2/-0 and lose all creature types until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: When all is taken away, all are equal.

data.name: Elvish Promenade
data.oracle_text: Create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token for each Elf you control.
data.flavor_text: The faultless and immaculate castes form the lower tiers of elvish society, with the exquisite caste above them. At the pinnacle is the perfect, a consummate blend of aristocrat and predator.

data.name: Faerie Tauntings
data.oracle_text: Whenever you cast a spell during an opponent's turn, you may have each opponent lose 1 life.
data.flavor_text: Beneath the fae's constant pranks runs a subtler undercurrent of mockery: the influence of Oona, their hidden queen.

data.name: Feudkiller's Verdict
data.oracle_text: You gain 10 life. Then if you have more life than an opponent, create a 5/5 white Giant Warrior creature token.
data.flavor_text:
"There are all kinds of strengths, but if you have strength of soul, the others will follow."
—Galanda Feudkiller

data.name: Fodder Launch
data.oracle_text:
As an additional cost to cast this spell, sacrifice a Goblin.
Target creature gets -5/-5 until end of turn. Fodder Launch deals 5 damage to that creature's controller.
data.flavor_text: Leave it to a boggart to come up with a projectile as disgusting as it is deadly.

data.name: Hunting Triad
data.oracle_text:
Create three 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens.
Reinforce 3—{3}{G} ({3}{G}, Discard this card: Put three +1/+1 counters on target creature.)
data.flavor_text: "Eyeblights are easy to track. Just follow the imperfections."

data.name: Merrow Commerce
data.oracle_text: At the beginning of your end step, untap all Merfolk you control.
data.flavor_text: Schools meet and mingle on Lorwyn's riverways. In the bustling interplay, the merrow renew their sense of community as they sharpen their wits and hone their trading skills.

data.name: Noggin Whack
data.oracle_text:
Prowl {1}{B} (You may cast this for its prowl cost if you dealt combat damage to a player this turn with a Rogue.)
Target player reveals three cards from their hand. You choose two of them. That player discards those cards.

data.name: Not of This World
data.oracle_text:
Counter target spell or ability that targets a permanent you control.
This spell costs {7} less to cast if it targets a spell or ability that targets a creature you control with power 7 or greater.

data.name: Obsidian Battle-Axe
data.flavor_text: It's the flint that sparks a warrior's rage.

data.name: Prowess of the Fair
data.oracle_text: Whenever another nontoken Elf is put into your graveyard from the battlefield, you may create a 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature token.
data.flavor_text: An elvish duel is a thing of beauty: the warriors' grace, the crash of steel, then the artful spray of blood.

data.name: Reach of Branches
data.oracle_text:
Create a 2/5 green Treefolk Shaman creature token.
Whenever a Forest enters the battlefield under your control, you may return Reach of Branches from your graveyard to your hand.
data.flavor_text: Growth has no limits.

data.name: Rebellion of the Flamekin
data.oracle_text: Whenever you clash, you may pay {1}. If you do, create a 3/1 red Elemental Shaman creature token. If you won, that token gains haste until end of turn. (This ability triggers after the clash ends.)

data.name: Sage's Dousing
data.oracle_text: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {3}. If you control a Wizard, draw a card.
data.flavor_text:
"Curse these merrows and their meddling! Since coming near the river, I can't so much as sneeze without being soaked."
—Ashling the Pilgrim

data.name: Skittering Invasion
data.oracle_text: Create five 0/1 colorless Eldrazi Spawn creature tokens. They have "Sacrifice this creature: Add {C}."
data.flavor_text:
"The brood spread far faster than we could kill it. I fear the worst is yet to come."
—*The War Diaries*

data.name: Summon the School
data.oracle_text:
Create two 1/1 blue Merfolk Wizard creature tokens.
Tap four untapped Merfolk you control: Return Summon the School from your graveyard to your hand.
data.flavor_text:
"When merrows talk, listeners grow fins."
—Kithkin saying

data.name: Thieves' Fortune
data.oracle_text:
Prowl {U} (You may cast this for its prowl cost if you dealt combat damage to a player this turn with a Rogue.)
Look at the top four cards of your library. Put one of them into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

data.name: Thornbite Staff
Veteran's Armaments
Aquitect's Will
data.oracle_text: Put a flood counter on target land. That land is an Island in addition to its other types for as long as it has a flood counter on it. If you control a Merfolk, draw a card.
data.flavor_text:
"You may want to hold your breath."
—Kellyg, merrow aquitect

data.name: Blades of Velis Vel
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Up to two target creatures each get +2/+0 and gain all creature types until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: "The changing kind suffers as we do. We must join as one to quench our tyrants!"

data.name: Boggart Birth Rite
data.oracle_text: Return target Goblin card from your graveyard to your hand.
data.flavor_text: Auntie excitedly held up the squalling newborn. "This one looks like Byoog! Maybe he'll tell us what he saw and felt in the beyond."

data.name: Bound in Silence
data.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature can't attack or block.
data.flavor_text: A fight put off forever is already won.

data.name: Consuming Bonfire
data.oracle_text:
Choose one —
• Consuming Bonfire deals 4 damage to target non-Elemental creature.
• Consuming Bonfire deals 7 damage to target Treefolk creature.
data.flavor_text:
"The elves use treefolk to drive us away. It is time to remove their tools."
—Vessifrus, flamekin demagogue

data.name: Crib Swap
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Exile target creature. Its controller creates a 1/1 colorless Shapeshifter creature token with changeling.

data.name: Crush Underfoot
data.oracle_text: Choose a Giant creature you control. It deals damage equal to its power to target creature.
data.flavor_text:
Five-toed grave
—Kithkin phrase meaning "a giant's footprint"

data.name: Eyeblight's Ending
data.oracle_text: Destroy target non-Elf creature.
data.flavor_text:
"Those without beauty are Lorwyn's greatest tumor. The winnowers have an unpleasant duty, but a necessary one."
—Eidren, perfect of Lys Alana

data.name: Faerie Trickery
data.oracle_text: Counter target non-Faerie spell. If that spell is countered this way, exile it instead of putting it into its owner's graveyard.
data.flavor_text: The fae are so quick and their life spans so short that it's difficult to get retribution for their pranks.

data.name: Giant's Ire
data.oracle_text: Giant's Ire deals 4 damage to target player or planeswalker. If you control a Giant, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: The only feeling greater than hurling something a mile is crushing something else with it that was really, really irritating you.

data.name: Gilt-Leaf Ambush
data.oracle_text: Create two 1/1 green Elf Warrior creature tokens. Clash with an opponent. If you win, those creatures gain deathtouch until end of turn. (Each clashing player reveals the top card of their library, then puts that card on the top or bottom. A player wins if their card had a higher mana value. Any amount of damage a creature with deathtouch deals to a creature is enough to destroy it.)

data.name: Lignify
data.oracle_text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature is a Treefolk with base power and toughness 0/4 and loses all abilities.
data.set_name: Duel Decks Anthology: Garruk vs. Liliana
data.flavor_text: Bulgo paused, puzzled. What was that rustling sound, and why did he feel so stiff? And how could his *feet* be so thirsty?

data.name: Morsel Theft
data.oracle_text:
Prowl {1}{B} (You may cast this for its prowl cost if you dealt combat damage to a player this turn with a Rogue.)
Target player loses 3 life and you gain 3 life. If this spell's prowl cost was paid, draw a card.

data.name: Nameless Inversion
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Target creature gets +3/-3 and loses all creature types until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: Just as a changeling's influence can have dramatic effects, so too can its sudden withdrawal.

data.name: Peppersmoke
data.oracle_text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn. If you control a Faerie, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: Like being trapped in a perpetual sneeze, faerie-dust poisoning is both exhilarating and agonizing.

data.name: Rootgrapple
data.oracle_text: Destroy target noncreature permanent. If you control a Treefolk, draw a card.
data.flavor_text:
"All the sylvan secrets of this world are etched between my rings. The skinfolk's metal aberrations can rot between my roots."
—Colfenor, the Last Yew

data.name: Shields of Velis Vel
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Creatures target player controls get +0/+1 and gain all creature types until end of turn.
data.flavor_text: Changelings can alter shape based on what the beings around them desire most.

data.name: Stream of Unconsciousness
data.oracle_text: Target creature gets -4/-0 until end of turn. If you control a Wizard, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: Dreams are tempting because one is so powerful in them. Dreams are dangerous because that power is a lie.

data.name: Surge of Thoughtweft
data.oracle_text: Creatures you control get +1/+1 until end of turn. If you control a Kithkin, draw a card.
data.flavor_text: Kithkin weave together their very thoughts, creating a depth of cooperation unknown to other races.

data.name: Tarfire
data.oracle_text: Tarfire deals 2 damage to any target.
data.flavor_text:
"After Auntie brushed the soot from her eyes, she discovered something wonderful: the fire had turned the goat into something that smelled delicious."
—A tale of Auntie Grub

data.name: Violet Pall
data.oracle_text: Destroy target nonblack creature. Create a 1/1 black Faerie Rogue creature token with flying.
data.flavor_text: A faerie is the offspring of Oona and mischief.

data.name: Warren Weirding
data.oracle_text: Target player sacrifices a creature. If a Goblin is sacrificed this way, that player creates two 1/1 black Goblin Rogue creature tokens, and those tokens gain haste until end of turn.
data.flavor_text:
"And that's when it was discovered that boggarts have just half a brain."
—*The Book of Other Folk*

data.name: Wings of Velis Vel
data.oracle_text:
Changeling (This card is every creature type.)
Until end of turn, target creature has base power and toughness 4/4, gains all creature types, and gains flying.
data.flavor_text: Changeling magic grants unusual wishes.
